===Kings===
All but three of the [[Kings of France]] are buried in the basilica, as well as a few other monarchs. The remains of the earlier monarchs were removed from the destroyed [[Abbey of St Genevieve]]. Some of the prominent of these are:

* [[Clovis I]] (465 - 511)
* [[Childebert I]] (496 - 558)
* [[Ar<U+00E9>gonde]] (c.515 - c.573)
* [[Fredegonde]] (Wife of [[Chilperic I of Neustria]]) (? - 597)
* [[Dagobert I]] (603 - 639)
* [[Clovis II]] (635 - 657)
* [[Charles Martel]] (686 - 741)
* [[Pippin the Younger]] (714 - 768) and his wife [[Bertrada of Laon]] (726-783)
* [[Carloman I]] King of the Franks (c.751 - 771)
* [[Charles the Bald]] (823 - 877) (his monument was melted down) and his wife, [[Ermentrude of Orl<U+00E9>ans]] (823 - 869)
* [[Carloman, King of the West Franks|Carloman]] (866 - 884)
* [[Robert II the Pious]] (972<U+2013>1031) and [[Constance of Arles]] (c. 986 - 1032)
* [[Henry I of France|Henry I]] (1008<U+2013>1060)
* [[Louis VI of France|Louis VI]] (1081<U+2013>1137)
* [[Louis VII of France|Louis VII]] (1120<U+2013>1180) and [[Constance of Castile]] (1141<U+2013>1160)
* [[Philip II Augustus]] (1180<U+2013>1223)
* [[Charles I of Naples]] (1226<U+2013>1285), king of the Two Sicilies (1266<U+2013>85). An effigy covers his heart burial.
* [[Philip III the Bold]] (1245<U+2013>1285)
* [[Philip IV the Fair]] (1268<U+2013>1314) and [[Isabella of Aragon]] (1247&nbsp;<U+2013> 1271)
* [[Leo V of Armenia]] (1342<U+2013>1393)
* [[Louis XII of France]] (1462<U+2013>1515)
* [[Francis I of France|Francis I]] (1494<U+2013>1547)
* [[Henry II of France|Henry II]] (1519<U+2013>1559) and [[Catherine de' Medici]] (1519&nbsp;<U+2013> 1589)
* [[Francis II of France|Francis II]] (1544&nbsp;<U+2013> 1560)
* [[Charles IX of France|Charles IX]] (1550<U+2013>1574) (no monument)
* [[Henry III of France|Henry III]] (1551<U+2013>1589), also King of Poland (heart burial monument)
* [[Henry IV of France|Henry IV]] (1553<U+2013>1610)
* [[Louis XIII of France|Louis XIII]] (1601&nbsp;<U+2013> 1643)
